33 SUMMARY
3344 This amendment removes the requirement for the Wabanaki studies specialist to make
3355 recommendations on the funding of Wabanaki studies instruction. The amendment
3366 removes from the bill statutory language that requires the Department of Education to fund
3377 the work of the specialist and contracted advisors, as well as for the implementation of a
3388 teacher education program. The amendment authorizes the State Board of Education to
3399 adopt rules to require a Wabanaki studies component for teacher certification and requires
4400 the board to evaluate whether to adopt such rules no later than July 1, 2026. The
4411 amendment requires that the department begin study of the Wabanaki studies curricula at
4422 least biannually beginning July 1, 2026. The amendment also adds an appropriations and
